    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@krabradosty Thanks for identifying that bug! It's fixed in the latest release. \r\n\r\nUnfortunately, while looking into this issue, it's been discovered that that `web3` has it's own hardcoded wait limit: 50 blocks. (Code [here](https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js/blob/develop/lib/web3/contract.js#L105-L115)). \r\n\r\nFor the moment anyway, to be mined via `web3` (which Truffle uses), you'll have to set your deployment gas price high enough to get picked up within 50 blocks.\r\n\r\nClosing, thanks for your help.",
